<p>My goal is to write a program that can assist the driver by keeping the robot’s heading at a constant angle while not steering. I have something that works, but I want to rewrite this code to do the same thing but without using a while loop as it’s causing issues elsewhere in the program. The issue I’m running into is I don’t know how to store the “headingAngle” without using a while loop to prevent it from being overwritten.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2021-12-06T21:27:48.466Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":21,"reads":110,"readers_count":109,"score":127.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":397883,"topic_slug":"need-help-with-gyro-assisted-teleop","display_username":"Forrest Lasell","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/0/4/04d144aa378311e50da14c4e1b3cc8c6243dde62.png","internal":true,"reflection":false,"clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":47975,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/need-help-with-gyro-assisted-teleop/397883/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true,"can_vote":false},{"id":2980206,"name":"Peter Johnson","username":"Peter_Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png","created_at":"2021-12-06T22:55:46.927Z","cooked":"<p>You can put variables into the class level (these are called member variables), e.g. before the <code>@Override</code> in your screenshot.  These often have a prefix, e.g. <code>m_</code> to indicate they’re member variables.  When you first transition into the throttle/turning state (this will require another member variable to store the previous state), you’ll store the initial heading angle, and then use that value on later loop iterations.</p>
<p>So something like this:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">boolean m_prevInDriveStraight;
double m_headingAngle;

@Override
public void teleopPeriodic() {
  ...
  boolean inDriveStraight = isThrottle &amp;&amp; !isTurning;
  if (inDriveStraight) {
    if (!m_prevInDriveStraight) {  // initial entry into state
      m_headingAngle = ahrs.getYaw();
    }
    double error = m_headingAngle - ahrs.getYaw();
    double steerAssist = drive_kP * error;
    robotDrive.curvatureDrive(controller.getRawAxis(1), steerAssist, false);
  } else {
    robotDrive.curvatureDrive(controller.getRawAxis(1), controller.getRawAxis(4) / contDiv, quickTurn);
  }
  m_prevInDriveStraight = inDriveStraight;  // store previous state
  ...
}
</code></pre>
<p>Note that when isThrottle is false or inTurning is true, the heading angle will get reset (the next time they satisfy the inDriveStraight condition).  Not sure if that’s what you want.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2021-12-10T06:54:17.697Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":96,"readers_count":95,"score":34.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":397883,"topic_slug":"need-help-with-gyro-assisted-teleop","display_username":"Peter Johnson","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":13575,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Volunteer WPILib Developer, CSA"},"post_url":"/t/need-help-with-gyro-assisted-teleop/397883/2","custom_user_title":"Volunteer WPILib Developer, CSA","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":2980208,"name":"Forrest Lasell","username":"ForrestB3","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/f/47e85d/{size}.png","created_at":"2021-12-06T23:17:13.567Z","cooked":"<p>Thank you so much! I’ll it out tonight at practice and let you know how it goes <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/slight_smile.png?v=9" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:"></p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2021-12-06T23:17:13.567Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"inc